ANTHRAX, HUMAN, BOVINE - BANGLADESH (06): (SIRAJGANJ)
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Wed 25 Aug 2010
Source: bdnews24.com [edited]
<http://www.bdnews24.com/details.php?id=171715&cid=2>


163 get anthrax, with 12 new cases
----------------------------------
Another 12 people have been infected with anthrax in Sirajganj. With
this the total number of anthrax patients reached 163 on Wednesday
[25 Aug 2010]. They are from Shahzadpur, Belkuchi, Kamarkhand, and a
newly affected Tarash sub-districts in Sirajganj.

The victims' [ages were] 40, 30, 18, 35 from Kamalpur village of
Shahzadpur; 22 from Gainakandi village of Belkuchi; 28 from Char
Rasulallapur village of Tarash; 35, 22, 55, 18, 20, and 20 from
Thakurjheepara village of Kamarkhand Upazila [sub district].

District sanitary inspector Ramchandra Saha said public awareness
programmes like discussion meeting on prevention and cure to anthrax
were held in Sirajganj. Orientation programmes on anthrax were held
at Belkuchi and Kamarkhand. World Health Organisation delegate Selina
Rahman and the Institute of Epidemiology Disease Control and Research
(IEDCR) chief scientific officer Subodh Kumar Kundu were present.

Every cattle will be vaccinated within 2 weeks by 37 teams,
coordinated by deputy commissioner Aminul Islam and district
livestock officer Mohammad Safiul Islam.

